@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@
+# FocusedEditableTextOptions Object
+
+* `mode` string (optional) - The text range to read. Can be `value`,
+  `surrounding`, or `full`. Default is `full`.
+* `maxLength` number (optional) - Maximum number of UTF-16 code units to return
+  in `text`. Must be between `1` and `1000000`. Default is `100000`.
+
+When `mode` is `value`, Electron reads Chromium's current focused input value
+snapshot when available. When `mode` is `surrounding`, Electron reads text
+around the current selection from Blink. When `mode` is `full`, Electron reads
+the full focused editable DOM text on a best-effort basis and truncates around
+the current selection if the text is longer than `maxLength`.
