+# FocusedEditableText Object
+
+* `frame` [WebFrameMain](../web-frame-main.md) - The frame that owns the
+  focused editable element.
+* `url` string - The current URL of `frame`.
+* `isMainFrame` boolean - Whether `frame` is the main frame of the WebContents.
+* `inputType` string - The current Chromium text input type for the focused
+  editable context. Can be `text`, `password`, `search`, `email`, `number`,
+  `telephone`, `url`, `date`, `dateTime`, `dateTimeLocal`, `month`, `time`,
+  `week`, `textArea`, `contentEditable`, `dateTimeField`, `null`, or
+  `unknown`.
+* `inputMode` string - The current input mode requested by the focused editable
+  context. Can be `default`, `none`, `text`, `tel`, `url`, `email`, `numeric`,
+  `decimal`, `search`, or `unknown`.
+* `inputAction` string - The current enter-key action requested by the focused
+  editable context. Can be `default`, `enter`, `done`, `go`, `next`,
+  `previous`, `search`, `send`, or `unknown`.
+* `text` string - The text snapshot selected by `mode`.
+* `selection` [FocusedEditableTextSelection](focused-editable-text-selection.md) -
+  The current selection range relative to `text`.
+* `composition` [FocusedEditableTextComposition](focused-editable-text-composition.md) -
+  The current IME composition state relative to `text` when it is fully inside
+  the returned text snapshot.
+* `source` string - How `text` was obtained. Can be `text-input-state`,
+  `surrounding-selection`, or `dom`.
+* `mode` string - The requested mode used for this snapshot. Can be `value`,
+  `surrounding`, or `full`.
+* `isPartial` boolean - Whether `text` is a partial snapshot of the focused
+  editable text.
+
+`selection.start` and `selection.end` are UTF-16 offsets into `text`, so
+`text.slice(selection.start, selection.end)` returns the selected text.
