+#### `contents.getFocusedEditableText([options])` _Experimental_
+
+* `options` [FocusedEditableTextOptions](structures/focused-editable-text-options.md) (optional)
+
+Returns `Promise<FocusedEditableText | null>` - resolves with a
+[`FocusedEditableText`](structures/focused-editable-text.md) snapshot for the
+focused editable element, or `null` if no focused editable text can be read.
+
+The returned `selection.start` and `selection.end` offsets are relative to the
+returned `text` string. The selected text can be read with:
+
+```js
+const selectedText = info.text.slice(info.selection.start, info.selection.end)
+```
+
+Password inputs return `null`. Custom editors backed by DOM-editable content are
+handled on a best-effort basis. Editors backed by canvas, virtual documents, or
+application-internal models may only expose the focused DOM control.
+
 #### `contents.isLoading()`

 Returns `boolean` - Whether web page is still loading resources.
